ne server, multiple agent voices",["$","$L5",null,{"id":"the-problem-one-server-multiple-agent-voices"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["protoWorkstacean routes messages to multiple agents — Quinn for code review and triage, Ava for features and planning, Frank for infrastructure. When these agents post responses back to GitHub, Discord, or Plane, they should appear as distinct identities. A Quinn review should show ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"protoquinn[bot]"}],", not a generic bot. An Ava feature creation comment should show ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"protoava[bot]"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"This matters because:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"className":"x:[:is(ol,ul)_&]:my-[.75em] x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:list-disc x:ms-[1.5em]","children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Attribution"}]," — humans reading GitHub issues can tell at a glance whether Quinn or Ava made the observation"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Filtering"}]," — bots can be muted or filtered selectively"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Trust signals"}]," — a PR review from ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"protoquinn[bot]"}]," carries the implicit context that this is a code-focused agent, not a general-purpose one"]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{"className":"x:my-[2em] nextra-border"}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"id":"how-it-works-github-app-identities","className":"x:tracking-tight x:text-slate-900 x:dark:text-slate-100 x:font-semibold x:target:animate-[fade-in_1.5s] x:mt-10 x:border-b x:pb-1 x:text-3xl nextra-border","children":["How it works: GitHub App identities",["$","$L5",null,{"id":"how-it-works-github-app-identities"}]]}],"\n","$L6","\n","$L7","\n","$L8","\n","$L9","\n","$La","\n","$Lb","\n","$Lc","\n","$Ld","\n","$Le","\n","$Lf","\n","$L10","\n","$L11","\n","$L12","\n","$L13","\n","$L14","\n","$L15","\n","$L16","\n","$L17","\n","$L18","\n","$L19","\n","$L1a","\n","$L1b","\n","$L1c","\n","$L1d","\n","$L1e","\n","$L1f","\n","$L20","\n","$L21","\n","$L22"]}]]}]]}]}],null,"$L23"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"aIlg1q43siquEH60mCfm_"}
6:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"Quinn and Ava each have their own GitHub App installation. Each app has an App ID and a private key (PKCS#1 PEM). The A2APlugin uses these to generate short-lived JWT tokens for GitHub API calls."}]
